  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Image Strategies**\n\nI\'ve hit a snag: the `generate_image` tool choked on a resource error, specifically a quota issue. No sweat, it\'s expected. My image selection strategy kicks in; if no known assets are available, it\'s fallback time. The strategy specifies picsum.photos for placeholders, but hold on, what about CSS? This opens up new possibilities.\n\n\n**Designing Visual Enhancements**\n\nOkay, I\'m now zeroing in on high-performance visual enhancements. The goal is crafting beautiful SVG gradients and inline assets for instant loading and a craft-focused aesthetic. I\'ll be creating custom mock illustrations and styled CSS designs\342\200\224think elegant gradients and cards with gold borders. My focus is now on constructing a rich and accurate menu for Uttar Pradesh cuisine. I\'ve begun creating `/src/data/menu.ts` to store this data, promoting modularity and reusability. I will be extracting the menu data from the OCR results.\n\n\n**Cataloging Menu Items**\n\nI\'ve got the Uttar Pradesh menu items formatted and ready for integration. I\'m focusing on organizing each dish with its description and price, essential for a functional, aesthetically pleasing menu. I\'m especially eager to incorporate the \"chef\'s pick\" and \"heritage\" designations. I\'m thinking of placing the Lassi variations in either the Varanasi section or the \"Elixir Collection,\" depending on the existing architecture.\n\n\n**Adding Menu Details**\n\nNow I\'m fleshing out the menu, diving into Uttar Pradesh\'s culinary gems. Currently, I\'m focusing on the Prayagraj section, adding details for each dish, including prices, descriptions, and special designations like \"CHEF\'S PICK\" or \"HERITAGE.\" I\'ve just added the items for Prayagraj, and am now adding a few for Agra, continuing to expand the menu database.\n\n\n**Expanding Menu Offerings**\n\nI\'m presently building out the Agra and Mathura menu sections. I\'ve finished adding the Agra dishes, including \"Agra Breakfast,\" \"Mughlai Paratha,\" and the Petha sweets. Now, I\'m focusing on Mathura, which has \"Golden Gram Crepe\" and \"Green Lentil Veil,\" aiming to balance culinary detail with appealing presentation. Finally I will add the Muradabad section.\n\n\n**Adding Lucknow\'s Selections**\n\nI\'m expanding the menu with Lucknow\'s culinary offerings. I\'m adding \"Golden Cradle\" (Basket Chaat) and \"Royal Biryani,\" ensuring each dish description highlights its unique flavors and heritage. I\'m noting prices and specific descriptions to enrich the user experience. Now I\'m preparing a beverage section.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
